      <abstract>
        <p>A novel benzimidazole derivative (<bold>2)</bold> was synthesized by hydrolyzing 4-[(5-chloro-3-methyl-1-phenyl-1<italic>H</italic>-pyrazol-4-yl)methylene]-2-phenyloxazol-5(4<italic>H</italic>)-one <bold>(1)</bold>, the azlactone precursor in an acidic medium and treating the product with <italic>o</italic>-phenylenediamine (OPDA) <italic>in situ.</italic> The structure of the title compound (<bold>2)</bold> was established on basis of FT-IR, <sup>1</sup>H-NMR, <sup>13</sup>C-NMR and mass spectral data.</p>
      </abstract>
